},{"section":5,"text":"She also mentions fatigue and malaise, especially in the early afternoon.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.064795,0.11864,0.11242,0.098473,0.095419,0.086276,0.081203,0.076629,0.070922,0.062293,0.067117,0.065815],"unified_progress":[0.085444,0.11818,0.1042,0.094687,0.093131,0.089602,0.084035,0.08514,0.075681,0.068089,0.057743,0.044066]},{"section":6,"text":"Fatigue can be a symptom of many things, but combined with joint pain, it might point towards an autoimmune condition.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049448,0.094275,0.10289,0.12176,0.097313,0.091222,0.088451,0.084364,0.078871,0.072185,0.064032,0.05519],"unified_progress":[0.0443,0.07644,0.094224,0.10405,0.10041,0.098996,0.098448,0.09498,0.088411,0.083443,0.068224,0.048079]},{"section":7,"text":"Looking at the physical exam, there's tenderness and synovial thickening in the small hand joints\u2014proximal interphalangeal and metacarpophalangeal joints.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037358,0.077726,0.096431,0.10619,0.10957,0.10424,0.10243,0.091414,0.083029,0.071767,0.063848,0.055996],"unified_progress":[0.036993,0.075359,0.094973,0.10534,0.11168,0.10608,0.10046,0.093352,0.093275,0.073651,0.060743,0.048089]},{"section":8,"text":"That's a classic sign of arthritis, possibly rheumatoid arthritis (RA) because those are the joints typically affected in RA.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035881,0.093941,0.10995,0.12115,0.10515,0.097187,0.092672,0.086585,0.07675,0.069191,0.059464,0.052079],"unified_progress":[0.028072,0.065584,0.087298,0.10153,0.10346,0.10775,0.1082,0.10078,0.09363,0.086633,0.068723,0.048347]},{"section":9,"text":"The involvement is symmetric, which is another clue.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037571,0.087067,0.10313,0.11854,0.10368,0.097383,0.093576,0.087567,0.080739,0.07381,0.063984,0.052952],"unified_progress":[0.030218,0.065276,0.084286,0.096096,0.10121,0.10118,0.10375,0.10261,0.097492,0.093566,0.07406,0.050252]},{"section":10,"text":"She also has similar symptoms in other joints like the feet, elbows, and ankles.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.050278,0.078365,0.087423,0.090756,0.095489,0.095029,0.095129,0.092385,0.08891,0.082842,0.076863,0.06653],"unified_progress":[0.05369,0.079071,0.085685,0.091033,0.09575,0.096214,0.095917,0.095949,0.091982,0.086731,0.073083,0.054896]},{"section":11,"text":"Symmetric joint involvement is a hallmark of RA rather than, say, osteoarthritis which is more asymmetric.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037843,0.061901,0.077563,0.08827,0.093905,0.096797,0.10191,0.10188,0.098095,0.091479,0.080986,0.069373],"unified_progress":[0.034811,0.060346,0.081198,0.090132,0.096439,0.10447,0.10182,0.10006,0.096915,0.091768,0.078931,0.063119]},{"section":12,"text":"The lab result mentioned is an autoantibody directed against IgG.","dimension":10,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034351,0.067701,0.087329,0.097414,0.10228,0.10174,0.10042,0.093981,0.088973,0.083782,0.075589,0.066439],"unified_progress":[0.037197,0.072134,0.089536,0.099574,0.10541,0.10223,0.10028,0.094736,0.09362,0.080359,0.068885,0.056048]},{"section":13,"text":"Wait, that's a bit confusing because the most common autoantibodies in RA are rheumatoid factors (which are antibodies against IgG) and anti-CCP antibodies.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031629,0.062145,0.078998,0.09212,0.09957,0.10267,0.10559,0.10341,0.097151,0.088024,0.075474,0.063219],"unified_progress":[0.034234,0.066927,0.086571,0.097379,0.10287,0.11049,0.10639,0.098344,0.091818,0.084343,0.069314,0.051324]},{"section":14,"text":"So, detecting an anti-IgG autoantibody could be pointing towards RA.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03102,0.054366,0.071933,0.08